This is a map set in a trainstation (A DER). I did what I did in my other Half-Life 2 Deathmatch map. There is a train that goes by and the players must watch out for it. The two bombsites are a garden and the docks. I thought about the layout alot when I was making this map. I literally worked on this map ANY chance I got. A week and a half of constant mapping. 

COOL POINTS OF THE MAP: 
-The train 
-MAKE SURE TO GET HIT BY THE TRAIN! It honks it horn when it hits a player and the player goes FLYING. 
-The docks explode when the bomb explodes 
-The garden fountain explodes when the bomb explodes. 
-REALLY fun to play with bots or people. Nothing cooler than hearing the train horn in the distance and then looking up to see who got smaked by it. (Especially with bots :D) 
-Bots play well in it

_aChangeLog.text: Beta 1 Change-Log: -slight Tweak to max player limit (slight increase Tweak) -Added Props to light sources for immersion (detail) -Added Phys_props to CT spawn (detail) -Slightly Trashed Storage room (detail) -Added railings around the top of the outdoor area (detail) -Added various decorative buildings to the map (detail) -added various decorative Props on top of the map (detail) -Minor detailing tweaks on the interior detail of the Blue shack (detail/tweaks) -Connected all sewer Lights with wires (detail) -Changed wall textures in Main Yard (detail/tweak)

_aLatestUpdates._sText: At this point in the maps development im quite happy with the way it is, So there probably won't be as many beta releases compared to the alpha, as any changes or tweaks may be minor in nature but i may add a 3D skybox as well as get around to the Radar at some point, though i do think it would be fine without it at this point.

_aChangeLog.text: -All Dev Textures replaced with nodraw (optimisation) -Changed geometry in T spawn-ladder shaft -Added Detail in CT spawns -Added Detail in CT's Path to B -Added Detail in T's path to Office -Added Detail in Bombsite B's storage room thing (IDK what's its called so i'll just refer to it as B storage) -Added Red strip to the main outdoor area (a nice bit of detail) -minor lighting tweaks -also placed radio in B storage room

_aLatestUpdates._sText: This is probably going to be the last alpha release before i switch over to beta.

De_toxin_50 release notes

Map Name: de_toxin_50
Author: Scott "eXpendabLe" Hilbrands
Release Date: 05.05.05

Counter-Strike:Source Game Level

* Number of Spawn Points: 50 - 25t and 25ct

* Info:
Counter-Terrorists must prevent the bombing of toxic storage tanks in this industrial complex.

Terrorists: Destroy one of the storage tanks and release the toxins.

Other Notes: Layout of this map is straightforward: CT and Terror spawns are connected by an overhead passageway and a drainage canal. Designed to provide both sniping and close quarters combat.

Fix List/Updates - 05/05/05
1. increased spawn points to 50
2. fixed "disapearing player" spots
3. fixed fading barrels/props
4. added ambient water sounds
5. reworked Bomb Spot A area
6. various geometry tweaks.

Installation Instructions:
Place contents of this zip file into the following directory:

C:\Program Files\Valve\Steam\SteamApps\steam_name_here\counter-strike source\cstrike\maps 



=========================================================================================

Please report bugs and or suggestions to:

shilbrands@cox.net

Enjoy!
